proof.p:
We derive a formula for the C, converting questions to Boolean propositions for compactness:

\begin{split}
C_{i j} &= \textrm{Warp thead } j \textrm{ is lifted when treadle } i \textrm{ is pressed}\\
		& = (\textrm{harness }1 \textrm{ is lifted by treadle } i\textrm{ and harness }1\textrm{ is connected to  warp thread} j)\textrm{ or } \\
		& \quad  (\textrm{harness }2 \textrm{ is lifted by treadle } i\textrm{ and harness }2\textrm{ is connected to  warp thread} j)\textrm{ or } \cdots\\
		& = T_{1i}H_{1j }+T_{2i}H_{2j }+\cdots \\
		& = T^{t}_{i1}H_{1j }+T^{t}_{i2}H_{2j }+\cdots \\
		& = \left(T^tH\right)_{i j}
\end{split}

Therefore, C= T^t H

Now we can compute W.

\begin{split}
W_{i j} &= \textrm{Warp thead } j \textrm{ is lifted above weft thread } i\\
		&= L_{i 1}C_{1j }+ L_{i 2}C_{2j }+\cdots \\
		& = (L C)_{i j}\\
		&= \left(L T^t H\right){}_{i j}
\end{split}
